summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) and 2,2,4-trimethylpentane are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) relevant to the study of chemical metabolism. However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship or interaction. The focus is primarily on the metabolism of TCE and the effects of various substances on its metabolism, without specific reference to 2,2,4-trimethylpentane.
